JOHANNESBURG - Telkom is to create a separate and wholly owned subsidiary to focus on its property portfolio.The parastatal confirmed on Monday its plans to separate its telecoms and real estate business. A stock market listing for the latter may follow.READ: Has Telkom turned the corner?Telkom says the property portfolio could offer a strong additional revenue stream.The company holds one of the largest real estate portfolios in the country.Analysts say the move is part of Telkom CEO Sipho Maseko s turnaround strategy. eNCA